a freighter being pulled by tugboats through a 
calumet river channel struck an aging railroad drawbridge friday 
bringing down the rusted span on the vessel authorities said the 
27member crew escaped injury 
the bridge and the boat are pretty much together right now 
said coast guard petty officer brian zelner 
the 590foot cypriotregistered freighter had just unloaded 
steel and was about a mile from lake michigan when the accident 
occurred shortly after 8 pm zelner said he said he had no 
immediate report on damage 
the freighter which was headed for lake michigan hit the 50to 
70footlong bridge which was in the open position said police 
sgt ron magro 
howard schillaci a sales clerk at a fishing gear store said he 
saw the accident from his shop window 
the ship was coming through and all of a sudden the bridge 
broke loose and came down on top of the back end of the ship 
schillaci said it sounded like a car accident 
magro said the baltimore and ohio bridge is about 100 years old 
is still used although he said it believes only by freight trains 
zelner said the bridge was 19 feet above the water when closed 135 
feet when open 
its old and i know its real rusted schillaci said 
