<TEXT>
a strong earthquake rocked northern japan on 
saturday morning the central meteorological agency said national 
police said there were no immediate reports of damage or casualties 
the agency said the quake centered off the coast of the 
northernmost island of hokkaido occurred at 1059 am 959 pm 
friday edt and measured a preliminary reading of 64 on the 
richter scale 
cma officials said the quake registered a four on the japanese 
scale of seven in kushiro 560 miles northwest of tokyo three in 
aomori 360 miles away and one in tokyo 
a tremor measuring five on the japanese scale can crack walls 
overturn gravestones and damage chimneys a four will shake houses 
and topple vases 
the openended richter scale measures the magnitude of a quake 
at its epicenter according to ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs 
an earthquake of five on the scale is considered very strong 
and a six severe capable of widespread damage near the 
epicenter 
every increase of one digit represents a tenfold increase in 
magnitude thus a reading of 75 would be 10 times stronger than 
one of 65 
the japanese scale measures the intensity of an earthquake at a 
particular location and is not convertible to the richter scale 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

