<TEXT>
an arabamerican lobbying group is praising a 
california companys decision to stop selling tear gas to israel 
saying the move is a symbolic victory for palestinians 
we hope the decision will send a signal to israeli prime 
minister yitzhak shamir that he can no longer count on corporate 
americas cooperation in denying the palestinians their most basic 
human rights the americanarab antidiscrimination committee 
said in a statement friday 
the statement came after an official of transtechnology corp 
of sherman oaks calif said the board of directors had agreed to 
the companys new policy under which the firm will no longer sell 
tear gas to israel 
we want some breathing room said burl alison 
transtechnologys vice president describing the companys decision 
the company which makes tear gas at its federal laboratories in 
saltsburg pa had been under tremendous pressure from 
arabamerican groups and human rights activists to stop the sales 
she said 
the groups claimed the israelis have misused the tear gas in 
quelling palestinian demonstrations in the west bank and gaza 
strip causing deaths and injuries 
yossi gal a spokesman at the israeli embassy disputed 
allegations that his government deliberately has misused tear gas 
and pointed out that tear gas is routinely used by police and 
military forces around the world 
he described as wildly exaggerated the allegations that as many 
as 40 people in the israelioccupied west bank and gaza strip had 
been killed by improper use of tear gas 
mrs alison did not rule out the possibility that tear gas sales 
would resume but she said that would happen only if the company 
can determine the chemical crowdcontrol agent is being handled 
properly 
there are no outstanding contracts to ship tear gas to israel 
but mrs alison said the israelis wanted to buy more gas from 
transtechnology 
israel has bought 120000 tear gas grenades or projectiles from 
us companies under the us governments military sales program 
since december 
state department officials have defended the sale of tear gas to 
israel on the grounds that it is an effective way of curbing 
violent demonstrations alternative methods of controlling crowds 
could be much more lethal they say 
physicians for human rights a bostonbased group has expressed 
concern that the israelis may not be following proper handling 
directions for tear gas which overcomes victims by causing severe 
irritation to the eyes skin and respiratory tract the group has 
called for more study into the effects of tear gas 
if used correctly the effects of tear gas are shortlived but 
the chemical agent can cause death particularly to infants and the 
elderly if it is fired into enclosed spaces there have been 
reports the israelis fired tear gas into a mosque and a hospital 
