<TEXT>
mayor richard s caliguiri the citys chief 
executive for more than a decade died of heart failure at age 56 
on the day he was scheduled to meet with doctors to discuss a 
possible heart transplant 
he was the kindest of men and always thought the best of 
others said city council president sophie masloff 70 who was 
sworn in as mayor friday about seven hours after caliguiris death 
mrs masloff a democrat becomes the citys first woman mayor 
she will complete caliguiris term which expires in january 1990 
and retain her council seat she said she would carry out 
caliguiris policies 
meanwhile friends associates and even former political foes of 
the late mayor praised him friday 
gov robert casey ordered flags on state property flown at 
halfstaff friday and called the late mayor a vibrant force for 
the good of our people our state and our nation 
his death is a tragic loss not only to the family he loved so 
deeply but to the city that has been his lifes work said us 
sen john heinz rpa 
