leukemia worldwide in patients treated with synthetic growth 
hormones said an increased risk had not been proven but even if it 
had it is not great enough to warrant withholding treatment 
there is no therapy that is riskfree said a statement by 
the lawson wilkins pediatric endocrine society which represents 
doctors and scientists working in the field because gh therapy 
is essential for optimal growth and development in gh deficient 
children it would be inappropriate and unwise to withhold such 
treatment from needy patients 
the incidence of leukemia among patients taking growth hormone 
worldwide is estimated at 1 in 21000 patientyears of treatment 
the society said while a reasonable estimate of the risk among 
nonpatients in the same age range is 1 in 42000 
the meetings were prompted by reports of leukemia in five 
japanese children who had received the treatment 
