material heavy water to be radioactive 
the norwegian government on wednesday said 15 tons of norwegian 
heavy water were illegally diverted in 1983 to an unknown 
destination by the duesseldorfbased rohstoff einfuhr firm 
the norwegian foreign ministry said rohstoff einfuhr stated that 
the heavy water was for scientific use in west germany and that its 
transport to another destination violated its licensing codes 
a official for rohstoff einfuhr denied the allegations 
we never left anyone in the dark that the shipment was 
intended for switzerland said a company official who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
the oslo newspaper verdens gang reported april 21 that the heavy 
water was flown on a liberianregistered west african airlines 
plane via basel switzerland to dubai then probably to a nuclear 
reactor in bombay india 
norway does not allow the export of heavy water to countries 
that have not signed the international nuclear nonproliferation 
agreement including india 
the ministry said it had so far determined only that the heavy 
water was sent by air freight to basel 
norwegian officials have asked west german officials to 
investigate 
heavy water or deuterium oxide is used as a coolant in some 
nuclear reactors but it can also be used to produce plutonium for 
use in nuclear arms india has several nuclear reactors that use 
heavy water 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

