hearing so much as a peep from iran 
it was as though iran did not exist this guided missile 
frigates captain edward mann told a pentagon media pool of 
fridays remarkably quiet voyage into the gulf of oman 
he said that no iranian gunboats or warships were sighted nor 
was there even any routine radio or radar conyact during the 
cruise which reached the open waters off oman near midnight 6 
pm edt 
they either learned a lesson or are planning something new 
one crewman said on the darkened bridge as the convoy left behind 
the strait 
the williams and a british destroyer hms gloucester made their 
way through the strait riding shotgun for a herd of tankers and 
merchant vessels 
about 10 ships traveled along with the warships in the largest 
convoy through the waterway since fierce usiranian naval clashes 
april 18 
other convoys are waiting for escort service at the mouth of the 
strait 
president reagan last week gave permission to the navy to aid 
ships flying other than american flags if they come under attack 
but cmdr mann said that when the british convoy moved alongside 
dubai it was little more than coincidence 
its a small ocean out here he said earlier on his 
sunbaked bridge as british and american helicopters crossed in the 
sky ahead of the convoy the deck temperature on the williams was 
measured at 126 degrees friday afternoon 
diplomatically i guess it has been difficult to get all these 
countries to agree to coordinate their polices he said but we 
keep in touch out here and i certainly would not sit by and watch 
if any aircraft attacked the gloucester 
the 3700ton guided missile frigate williams protected two 
kuwaitiowned but americanflagged oil tankers it was flanked by 
four tankers escorted by the 4000ton glouchester 
iraq on thursday said it hit an iranian naval target this has 
