transplant recipients 
doublelung transplants have been performed 30 times worldwide 
and only 12 times in north america three times at jackson and 
nine times at toronto general hospital under the auspices of the 
toronto university school of medicine 
eight of the toronto patients are still living but only one of 
the three from jackson remains alive university medical center 
officials attributed one of the two deaths to factors unrelated to 
either the surgery or respiratory ailments that led to the 
operations 
