kadar who in western eyes a villain of the 1956 hungarian 
tragedy gained a new image in the next three decades as a 
dedicated architect of political and economic liberalization aimed 
at improving hungarian life 
today hungary is one of the more prosperous of the soviet bloc 
countries one of the easiest to visit for westerners including 
refugees of 1956 and its citizens have the easiest time leaving 
hungarian reform does not serve as a model for moscow but 
