onto the street 
other tailors followed and the influx of tradesmen so upset 
wealthy doctors living in the fashionable residential neighborhood 
that they fled to harley street 
now savile row is threatened by new planning laws bright said 
until last summer light industry and offices were separate 
planning categories and permission was required to change from one 
to the other both now fall into a new general business category 
the government said it was trying to revitalize inner cities by 
loosening planning laws but bright said that means tailors 
workshops in savile row and adjoining soho can be redeveloped into 
more lucrative office space without official permission 
he expects rents to quadruple followed by tax increases some 
landlords already are asking about 95 a square foot he said 
it is an enormous threat there is no way the french would 
just pass up their haute couture industry and yet this government 
is quite prepared to write off the top of the british clothing 
industry as if it didnt matter 
bright said its difficult to find words to describe the 
pleasures of bespoke tailoring 
its an experience it is a feeling of confidence that you 
know that you are projecting just the image that you want to 
project the part of your personality that you want to speak we 
are in fact creating a portrait in cloth he said 
with a readymade suit you have to conform not only to a given 
set of measures but also to what the designer wants you to look 
like when he hasnt even seen you bright said 
a bespoke suit should last a decade providing it hangs in the 
closet for six days between wearings so the wool can recover its 
bounce hence the advice that a proper english gentleman owns 
seven suits one for each day of the week 
bright said savile row does 48 million annual business 
including 32 million overseas 
anderson and sheppard are known as the royal tailors although 
several windows on the row prominently display royal warrants 
proving they do business with buckingham palace 
pooles received it first royal warrant from napoleon and later 
outfitted ethiopias emperor haile selassie 
huntsman and sons which keeps saddles in each of its five 
fitting rooms made riding breeches for king edward viii who 
abdicated to marry the american wallis simpson 
</TEXT>
