have fled to the capital where a third of the countrys population 
of 3 million lives to escape fighting 
the battles started in november 1981 less than a 1 years after 
the sandinistas came to power in a revolutionary war that overthrew 
the distatorship of late president anastasio somoza 
the general mood is the government doesnt know what to do and 
the economic situation doesnt have any way out until there is 
peace and a new acceptable government said ramiro gurdian vice 
president of the antigovernment private enterprise council 
