<TEXT>
neither 
side blinked when us and iranian ships glided silently past each 
other saturday in their closest encounter since a naval battle 
three weeks ago 
the 3700ton guided missile frigate jack williams spotted the 
booshehr a 354foot iranian supply boat on early morning patrol 
after the williams crossed the tense strait of hormuz twice in less 
than 24 hours 
the two ships sailed within about 2500 yards of each other on 
opposite courses in the rolling blue seas about 20 miles east of 
abu musa a heavily fortified island where iran maintains a gunboat 
base and air field 
the ships passed without any radio or other routine 
acknowledgement in an area almost within range of irans landbased 
chinesemade silkworm missiles the us navy calls the area the 
silkworm envelope but the crew uses the nickname the 
wormhole 
they are probably on patrol like us tracking ship movement 
gathering information said lt cmdr mark van dyke 
the booshehrs presence attracted curious crewmembers and their 
cameras 
a minespotting crewman stood at the bow of the iranian boat a 
sign of an apparent split between the regular iranian navy and the 
countrys revolutionary guards who seem to lay mines with autonomy 
thats nice a lookout on the williams told reporters when 
he saw his counterpart on the drab gray iranian ship even they 
dont know where the mines are 
american officers said the booshehr is one of only a few 
sightings of iranian warships that have crept out of port since the 
april 18 fighting 
the williams was at the center of those clashes which took 
place near where the ships passed saturday the us navy said 
after the april 18 clashes that it sank an iranian frigate 
disabled a second and hit four other ships a major loss for 
irans small navy 
a calm has settled over the persian gulf since then despite 
iranian threats of retaliation 
its nice to see their entire navy passing joked a chief 
petty officer on the bridge 
however iran still has its fleet of gunboats and other vessels 
as well as the ability to lay mines and the us navy has tried to 
remain vigilant 
before meeting the iranian boat the williams had completed 
escorting two tankers through the strait and into the gulf of oman 
a british destroyer hms gloucester rode shotgun for four tankers 
in the same convoy 
it was as though iran did not exist cmdr edward mann 
captain of the williams said of the quiet trip 
