hancock the first signer of the declaration of independence in 
1776 lived in the beacon hill mansion most of his life one of 
bostons wealthiest men and later governor of massachusetts 
hancock received many a dignitary at the home including president 
george washington 
the mansion which had been built in 1733 for hancocks uncle 
was torn down 130 years later after the state failed to appropriate 
money to buy and preserve it the site now lies in front of a later 
west wing of the statehouse 
