an authoritative forecast for growing supplies and slack demand 
has many experts turning bearish on gold but others say the gold 
markets jaded reaction to recent economic indicators casts a cloud 
over any longrange predictions 
a new report gold crash risk or reality from the 
respected wefa group and metalsandmining consultant resource 
strategies inc lays out the case for sharply lower gold prices 
the researchers said steadily rising mine production and weak 
investor demand will force prices down from current levels of 
around 450 a troy ounce to 300 or 350 by the early 1990s and as 
low as 250 a troy ounce within five years 
investors and portfolio managers should not have long 
positions in gold at this time the study warns 
chicagobased gnp commodities is also forecasting a sharp drop 
in gold prices beginning next year to as low as 350 a troy ounce 
critics of the wefa report point out that gold prices have 
traditionally responded more to economic factors especially 
inflation fears than to supply factors but even some of those 
analysts foresee sharply lower gold prices 
peter cardillo commodity trading adviser for new yorkbased 
josephthal amp co predicts a rapid decline in gold prices to under 
400 a troy ounce within the next month 
cardillo said he disagreed with the wefa groups reasoning and 
based his forecast on golds high price relative to crude oil 
he said a troy ounce of gold on new yorks commodity exchange 
traditionally costs about 18 times the price of a barrel of west 
texas intermediate crude oil on the new york mercantile exchange 
he said he expected crude oil prices to average 20 a barrel 
over the next two years using cardillos simple rule of thumb 
that would put gold at 360 a troy ounce 
at the current price near 450 gold is somewhat overpriced 
cardillo said 
he said the inflated gold price stemmed from overdone fears of 
inflation 
i think we will have an uptick in inflation but certainly not 
anything to worry about he said i dont think were headed 
for a runaway inflation 
inflation is the main engine of the gold market because gold 
tends to hold its value during inflationary times 
the wefa group took the gold markets reluctance to rally on 
recent inflationary indicators as a signal that investor enthusiasm 
for gold is not as strong as it used to be 
that may be true many analysts have noted a drop in investor 
activity in all the financial markets since the stock markets 
plunge in october 
but gold prices also have refused to fall very far on 
deflationary signals making it difficult to mke any prediction 
about future price movement said david syphen vice president of 
metals and foreign exchange trading for merrill lynch capital 
markets inc 
gold has traded within a range of 440 to 460 a troy ounce 
since february 
we seem to have a high degree of stability to the market right 
now syphen said its just maintaining equilibrium for the 
time being 
