the sevenmonth cliffhanger for control of 
irving bank corp has reached a climax with both irving and its 
hostile suitor bank of new york co hinting at victory 
but the final results of the shareholder vote completed at 
irvings annual meeting friday wont be known until later this 
month 
irving stockowners had to choose between a slate of 16 incumbent 
directors that back a restructuring and friendly merger with banca 
commerciale italiana spa italys secondlargest bank and nominees 
from rival bank of new york 
irving chairman joseph a rice wearing a v for victory pin 
on his lapel said friday that he was optimistic about the vote 
why shouldnt i say we have this wrapped he told a news 
conference 
bank of new york spokesman owen brady also said we are very 
optimistic 
although the results are not expected to be released before a 
reconvened meeting may 24 both sides said they were confident 
based on preliminary proxy counts and conversations with 
institutional investors which hold about twothirds of irvings 
185 million common shares outstanding 
irving spokesman david santos said early counts showed about 
half of the 20 million voting shares which included preferred 
stock were in favor of irvings board but he cautioned that it 
was possible a number of those shares also were sent in duplicate 
to bank of new york 
