and many said they were angered that irving had not obtained a 
better deal 
theres no question in my mind that the bank of new york is 
trying to steal your bank said robert strougo a new york 
attorney representing 1600 voting shares theres no reason why 
this bank couldnt be sold for in excess of 100 a share 
bank of new york offered irving a cashandstock deal valued at 
around 14 billion when it first made its rare hostile bid seven 
months ago but it lowered its offer twice following the oct 19 
stock market crash 
irving has staunchly resisted bank of new yorks advances among 
its many defenses was to activate its poison pill antitakeover 
defense which is intended to make any hostile buyout prohibitively 
expensive 
rice said representatives from his bank and the bank of new york 
met as recently as two weeks ago but had no plans to resume talks 
in the meantime he said the company would continue to welcome 
offers from other potential suitors 
we are in discussion with anyone who will talk with us he 
told reporters were willing to consider the best proposition 
from anybody because we are dealing with a situation that was 
thrust upon us 
